    "order": 3,
    "type": "exercise",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "Problem 19.6 Show that:"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b004",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 4,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\n\\mathbb{E}_{\\tau}\\left[\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial\\theta}\\log[Pr(\\boldsymbol{\\tau}|\\theta)]b\\right]=0, \\tag{19.48}\n\\end{aligned}"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b005",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 5,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "where b does not depend on $\\tau$, so adding a baseline update doesn\u2019t change the expected policy gradient update."
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b006",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 6,
    "type": "exercise",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "Problem 19.7 $^{*}$ Suppose that we want to estimate a quantity E[a] from samples $a_{1}, a_{2} \\ldots a_{I}$ . Consider that we also have paired samples $b_{1}, b_{2} \\ldots b_{I}$ that are samples that co-vary with a where E[b] = $\\mu_{b}$ . We define a new variable:"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b007",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 7,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\na^{\\prime}=a-c(b-\\mu_{b}). \\tag{19.49}\n\\end{aligned}"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b008",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 8,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "Show that $\\mathrm{Var}[a']\\leq\\mathrm{Var}[a]$ when the constant c is chosen judiciously. Find an expression for the optimal value of c."
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b009",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 9,
    "type": "exercise",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "Problem 19.8 The estimate of the gradient in equation 19.34 can be written as:"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b010",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 10,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\n\\mathbb{E}_{\\tau}\\left[\\mathbf{g}[\\boldsymbol{\\theta}](r[\\pmb{\\tau}_{t}]-\\boldsymbol{b})\\right], \\tag{19.50}\n\\end{aligned}"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b011",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 11,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "where"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b012",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 12,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\n\\mathbf{g}[\\boldsymbol{\\theta},\\tau]=\\sum_{k=t}^{T}\\frac{\\partial\\log\\left[Pr(a_{t}|\\mathbf{s}_{t},\\boldsymbol{\\theta})\\right]}{\\partial\\boldsymbol{\\theta}}, \\tag{19.51}\n\\end{aligned}"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b013",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 13,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "and"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b014",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 14,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\nr[\\pmb{\\tau}]=\\sum_{k=t}^{T}r_{k}. \\tag{19.52}\n\\end{aligned}"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b015",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 15,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "Show that the value of b that minimizes the variance of the gradient estimate is given by:"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b016",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 16,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\nb=\\frac{\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\mathbf{g}[\\boldsymbol{\\theta},\\tau]^{2}r[\\pmb{\\tau}]\\right]}{\\mathbb{E}\\left[\\mathbf{g}[\\boldsymbol{\\theta},\\tau]^{2}\\right]}. \\tag{19.53}\n\\end{aligned}"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0401-b017",
    "page_key": 401,
    "order": 17,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "You will need to use the result from equation 19.35."
  },
